      "role": "user",
      "content": "My bad, I forgot I hadn't actually pasted the text yet. Here it is:\n\n\"4.2 Pricing Adjustments: The Supplier reserves the right to implement upward price adjustments of up to 5% during peak seasonal months (June-August) to account for market volatility. Such adjustments may be applied without further written negotiation, provided that the Supplier notifies the Client of the new rate via email 7 days prior to the start of the peak period.\"\n\nBased on that, does this contract give the supplier any unilateral rights to change the rates unexpectedly? I really need to know if I can count on our current budget staying solid.",
